OL,6,FCounsel for Mr Fulton said that his
OL,7,Fclient "did not appreciate just how
OL,8,Fserious the injuries were" and
OL,9,Fhighlighted that he had no relevant
OL,10,Fconvictions for violence.
OL,12,FMeanwhile, Mrs Fulton's defence
OL,13,Fsuggested he may have gone along with
OL,14,Fher husband's version of events due to
OL,15,F"a degree of dependence" on him and
OL,16,Fthat she had a "low risk" of
OL,17,Freoffending.
OL,19,FThe pair are set to be sentenced next
